{"id":3761990,"date":"2024-07-31T10:26:52","date_gmt":"2024-07-31T04:56:52","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/?p=3761990"},"modified":"2025-09-03T15:48:29","modified_gmt":"2025-09-03T10:18:29","slug":"how-online-ma-sociology-from-smu-helps-you-in-ugc-net-preparation","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/how-online-ma-sociology-from-smu-helps-you-in-ugc-net-preparation","title":{"rendered":"How online MA Sociology from SMU helps you in UGC NET preparation"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Every year, numerous students from all parts of the country apply for UGC NET exams to stand a chance for recruitment as Assistant Professors and to receive the privileged Junior Research Fellowship. These candidates are allowed to opt for the subject of their choice for the exam, one which best aligns with their area of specialization at the Master\u2019s level (minimum eligibility criteria to apply for UGC NET exams). Sociology is generally one of the most popular choices among UGC NET candidates, as nearly 100 questions in the exam are from Sociology, accounting for 200 marks.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>To facilitate your preparations for the competitive exam, Sikkim Manipal University offers an online MA Sociology program. With a host of common subjects in both the respective curricula, you can boost your chances at UGC NET success. Read more about how Sikkim Manipal University\u2019s MA Sociology for UGC NET is an ideal choice for you.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>UGC NET preparation with Sikkim Manipal University\u2019s MA Sociology<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>There\u2019s good news for all UGC NET entrants 2024! You can now boost your chances at UGC NET success with Sikkim Manipal University\u2019s <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/what-you-can-do-with-a-sociology-degree\">MA Sociology degree program<\/a>. This is because the latter entails many subjects in its comprehensive curriculum, which are common to UGC NET Sociology exam preparation as well. Let us look at some of these:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Sociological Theory<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Rural and Urban Transformations<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Family, Marriage, and Kinship<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Environment and Society<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Culture and Symbolic Transformations\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Research Methodology and Methods<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>UGC NET Sociology syllabus &#8211; Paper 1\u00a0<\/strong>\u00a0<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>As stated above, most subjects covered in both UGC NET and MA Sociology courses are quite similar, which makes it fairly easy for students to cope with preparations. Pursuing an MA in Sociology from Sikkim Manipal University can be quite helpful for UGC NET exam candidates. You can understand for yourself by looking at the syllabus prescribed for the UGC NET Sociology exam\u2019s Paper 1 below.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Paper 1 is a more generic test evaluating the general aptitude and teaching skills of the candidates. There are 50 questions with multiple-choice answers with a total of 100 marks. The UGC NET Sociology <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/online-ma-english-semester-wise-subjects\">syllabus<\/a> is classified into 10 key units that are detailed in the table below:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Units&nbsp;<\/strong><\/td><td><strong>Name of unit<\/strong><\/td><td><strong>Topics covered under each unit<\/strong><\/td><\/tr><tr><td>1<\/td><td>Sociological theory<\/td><td>Structuralism and functionalism, post-structuralism, post-modernism, and post-colonialism, classical sociological traditions, interpretative and Hermeneutic traditions, and Indian thinkers<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>2<\/td><td>Research methodology and methods<\/td><td>Formulating research design, techniques, conceptualizing social reality, and quantitative and qualitative methods&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>3<\/td><td>Basic concepts and institutions&nbsp;<\/td><td>Social institutions, social change and processes, sociological concepts, and social stratification&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>4<\/td><td>Rural and urban transformations&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/td><td>Urban society, rural, and peasant society<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>5<\/td><td>State, politics, and development&nbsp;<\/td><td>Social movements, protests and political processes in India<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>6<\/td><td>Economy and society<\/td><td>Factory and industry systems, gift, labor, exchange, capital, market, consumption, mode of production debates, tourism, property and property relations&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>7<\/td><td>Environment and society&nbsp;<\/td><td>Ecological degradation and migration, Social and cultural ecology: Diverse forms, environmental movements, agriculture, technological change, and biodiversity&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>8<\/td><td>Family, marriage, and kinship<\/td><td>Family and emotions, Theoretical approaches: Alliance, structure-functionalist, and cultural, honor killing, gender relations and power dynamics, domestic violence and crime against women<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>9<\/td><td>Science, technology, and society<\/td><td>E-governance and surveillance society, history of technological development, cyber crime, changing notions of space and time, food and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/the-role-of-todays-women-in-science-technology-and-innovation\">technology<\/a>, flows and boundaries<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>10<\/td><td>Culture and symbolic transformations<\/td><td>Communalism and secularism, moral economy, culture and environment, culture and politics, new religious movements<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>UGC NET Sociology syllabus &#8211; Paper 2<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Paper 2 of the UGC NET Sociology exam covers the subject of Sociology in great detail, unlike Paper 1 which is more generic. There are a total of 100 questions asked in the paper with a combined score of 200 marks.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The syllabus for Paper 2 is the same as the one tabulated above for Paper 1 Sociology UGC NET exam. However, there are some important topics that you can consider covering during your preparation, which are shared below. Note that most topics covered in the UGC NET Sociology syllabus are common to MA Sociology courses. Here are some key topics to particularly prepare for before the exam:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Sociology of education<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Sociology of health and medicine<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Tribal and Dalit studies<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Sociological thinkers<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Rural and urban Sociology<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Industrial Sociology<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Sociology of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/the-dynamic-interplay-between-social-media-and-globalization\">globalization<\/a><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Social change and development\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Classical Sociological theories<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Research methodology and methods<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Social institutions<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Sociological concepts and perspectives\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Gender and society\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Social stratification and mobility\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>UGC NET Sociology exam pattern\u00a0\u00a0<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To better understand the nature of the examination, shared below is the UGC NET Sociology exam pattern for your reference <em>(Source: <\/em><a href=\"https:\/\/www.shiksha.com\/sarkari-exams\/teaching\/articles\/ugc-net-sociology-syllabus-blogId-142619\"><em>https:\/\/www.shiksha.com\/sarkari-exams\/teaching\/articles\/ugc-net-sociology-syllabus-blogId-142619<\/em><\/a><em>).&nbsp;<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Paper<\/strong><\/td><td><strong>No. of questions<\/strong><\/td><td><strong>Marking parameters<\/strong><\/td><td><strong>Marks given<\/strong><\/td><td><strong>Total marks allotted&nbsp;<\/strong><\/td><\/tr><tr><td>1<\/td><td>50<\/td><td>Correct answer<\/td><td>+2<\/td><td>100<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>2<\/td><td>100<\/td><td>Correct answer<\/td><td>+2<\/td><td>200<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Total marks<\/strong><\/td><td>150<\/td><td>&#8211;<\/td><td>&#8211;<\/td><td>300<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>Note: <\/em><\/strong>There is no negative marking or mark deduction for any incorrect or unattempted answer by the candidate.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Why pursue online MA Sociology<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>As observed in this blog, most subjects taught in MA Sociology courses are common to those covered in UGC NET Sociology exams. This means that students appearing for UGC NET can get help from Sikkim Manipal University\u2019s MA Sociology degree program offered online on the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/top-scholarships-at-online-manipal\">Online Manipal platform<\/a>.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>A list of some of these common subjects has already been shared at the beginning of this blog for your easy reference. Covering these topics in the online MA Sociology course by Sikkim Manipal University can provide a boost to your UGC NET preparations, simplifying those topics for you and also helping you understand them better. Moreover, the MA Sociology degree prepares you to work in society upon graduation with a deeper understanding of the issues and problems concerning it &#8211; a valuable skill desirable in UGC NET exam candidates.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Conclusion<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Sociology is one of the most popular choices for UGC NET examinations in the country, as it is also the highest scoring for students. Since one of the primary prerequisites for attempting the national competitive test is a Master\u2019s degree, it can be helpful to pursue an MA in Sociology in parallel. Some of these reasons have been discussed in this blog.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Most subjects in the course curriculum are similar to those you need to study for the UGC NET exam and this would be particularly helpful to you in your preparation process. Also, the MA Sociology program by Sikkim Manipal is designed to equip students with essential skills such as analytical thinking, critical assessment, and effective communication, all of which can come in handy in dealing with complex sociological concepts.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Every year, numerous students from all parts of the country apply for UGC NET exams to stand a chance for recruitment as Assistant Professors and to receive the privileged Junior Research Fellowship. These candidates are allowed to opt for the subject of their choice for the exam, one which best aligns with their area of [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":19,"featured_media":1872487,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[610],"tags":[19,222],"class_list":["post-3761990","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-master-of-arts","tag-online-degree","tag-online-ma-in-sociology"],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v27.5 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/product\/yoast-seo-wordpress\/ -->\n<title>How online MA Sociology from SMU helps you in UGC NET preparation - Online Manipal<\/title>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"MA Sociology students find UGC NET preparations easier, how does an online MA Sociology from SMU complements UGC NET exam study.\" \/>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/3761990\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:locale\" c